<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="754" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2760: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Commissioner in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-12T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 12,
                                        1923—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>6. Your 62, November 9, 9 a.m., last paragraph.</p>
                        <p>Department has no objection to the modification of Article 2 of the Plan
                            of Evacuation in the manner suggested by you. The Department takes this
                            opportunity to express its gratification for the agreement which you
                            have been able to bring about.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>